snippet.textDisplay:
I completely cut out all news sources when Trump became president because I got sick of hearing about it (lasted I checked every journalism-based company is still posting about him nonstop). I have no idea what's going on in the world. We could be 2 years into a zombie apocalypse. I'm Canadian and Trump is somehow considered both local and national news. There are no RSS feeds for top stories that aren't political. No feeds for actual breaking news. It seems the entirety of modern journalism has forgotten about real news. Instead, it just keeps blatantly bringing up its agenda. Every predictable post trying for clickbait or controversy so their company profit increases. This may be a foreign concept these days, but the news isn't supposed to be exciting or controversial. It's supposed to be boring and its purpose is supposed to be for sharing raw unbiased information.
For example, Last Week Tonight isn't a news program. It's an entertainment and opinion program and it delivers both well. CNN, NBC, Fox, etc. are also entertainment and news programs. The difference is that their entertainment method is annoying instead of funny and they disguise their opinions as fact while masquerading as news. Not only are people unaware that what they're seeing isn't news, but the journalists themselves don't realize they're just in the business of opinion and entertainment. A lot of people get off on hearing the horrible things that go on in the world, that is the entertainment, and it's made fun and opinionated and controversial to further your entertainment. I miss journalism that takes itself seriously and actually uses the news to inform the population of whats going on in an honest no-tricks and no hot sauce way. Share the real data, keep opinions and biases and unconfirmed data to yourselves. I'd love to have push notification news, but I can't even find real news. Some day I could die because I miss an important push notification from a news source or RSS feed that usually just talks about some dumb president nobody likes. Wasn't news delivered in a monotone voice early in its broadcasting? That sure would be nice.
